messages.text: Look, I’m not in the mood to play games.
Not really. I work there. I’m there all the time.
How am I supposed to guess when you won’t tell me anything?!
You want me to remember last Tuesday?
Oh! Are you that girl who came in and bought that killer dress?
I didn’t give my number to anyone at the mall.
How’d you get this number then?
Come on. This has to be someone messing with me.
I don’t have time for this.
I think you know what it means.
What’s this about? Can you please tell me?
I’m me. WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?!
Okay, I’m done. You’re getting blocked.
How’d you do that? I just blocked you.
What happened at your job, Darryl?
How did you know about that??
Do you think I don’t know?
I lost it, okay? Are you happy?
I freaked out on a customer.
He was being rude to me.
What did you do to him?
I don’t have to tell you anything anyway! Who are you?
What did you do to the customer, Darryl?
Why am I even talking to you?! I’m blocking you!!
What did you do to the customer, Darryl?
What did you do to the customer after your boss fired you, Darryl?
But it is my business, Darryl.
It was something you shouldn’t hit a person with, wasn’t it Darryl?
And they didn’t get up this time, did they?
And they didn’t talk back anymore, did they?
And no one saw you, did they?
That’s it? That’s what this is about?! You saw me do it?!
No, Darryl. That would have been impossible.
It’s hard to observe something when you’re the one doing it.
Of course, duh. I’m on it with you!!
What the hell are you talking about?!
Darryl looks down at his hands.
His phone is nowhere to be seen.
All he can see are his two clenched fists.
But you’ve known that all along, haven’t you?
And you know what you need to do now.
Darryl starts sobbing uncontrollably until he can barely breathe.
After the sobs start to subside, he picks up his phone and dials 911.
I need to confess to a murder…
Darryl was a minor, so he only had to serve ten years for the murder he committed.
When he was released from prison, he made sure his temper never got out of control.
And “Unknown” never contacted Darryl on his phone again.
